The paper discusses a many-core architecture designed for experimentation with many-core applications and operating systems, which suggests that it could fit into the categories of computer architecture (cs.AR), operating systems (cs.OS), and parallel computing (cs.PF). The paper also discusses energy and computational performance, which could place it in the categories of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) and systems and control (cs.SY).
